games people played, some were from RL nicknames, some were from books they've read. <BR>  <BR>  <BR> We did this on my guild webboard, and it was neat to see how others named themselves, maybe you'll also enjoy it. <BR>  <p><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>Sir Replay Promisekeeper<br>L50 Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<br>Shadowed Souls<br>Cazic-Thule Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ureplay.showPublicProfile>replay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/4/00 3:19:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cazic-thule.com/replay/face02a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did you get your Paladin name?</span><hr size=1> ---cut and paste from guild webboard--- <BR>  <BR>  <BR> Back when people had to dial-up to each bulletin board with a 2400baud or 14400baud modem, alias were recommended over using your real name. This was even more true in the BBS underground. I know I didn't want common alias like &quot;Wolverine&quot; or &quot;Killer&quot;, and I just somehow thought of the alias &quot;Replay&quot;.  <BR>  <BR> This was before Musicland had it's little &quot;Replay&quot; membership card, before the &quot;Replay TV&quot; T.V. program recorder (so that you can watch T.V. shows later), but not before that Arcade magazine named &quot;Replay&quot;. <BR>  <BR> I actually met some old BBS aquiantances in DOOM/Quake, then later on, I met some other BBS and/or Quaker friends in EQ. Sneeky, for those who recall his name, was in a rival CTF clan that we came across very often. <BR>  <BR> Don't intend to ever change it, and only came across one copycat, and that was during the BBS days. <BR>  <BR> Promisekeeper(s) is a Christian-based organization, I thought that would be the best way to represent my RL religious background and reason for playing a Paladin, and it's worked. ;) <p><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>Sir Replay Promisekeeper<br>L50 Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<br>Shadowed Souls<br>Cazic-Thule Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uvardendarketernal.showPublicProfile>Varden Darketernal</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/4/00 3:37:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> name origin</span><hr size=1> About 3 years ago, I went simply by Darksheer, am name which originated from a game seldom known called Nectropolis. So I ran around IRC with this name to only find out that I was often confused with a so called &quot;hacker&quot; with the same name. Not wanting any flack over it I decided to rename myself. Nothing came to mind. Well around the same time my life turned upside down. Lost my girlfriend, lost my chance for the college I wanted to go to, missed graduation becuase the school made an oversight on the classes I was supposed to take in order to graduate. So I had to take a full course in summer school. Well needless to say I was a mess. So I decided to take a name that would reflect me. At the time there seemed no way out of Darkness, and well Dark had come from my previous name. So It began with Dark, now with such and endless void of it, I had an eternal damnation I sort of gave to myself. So there you had it Darketernal was my name. Now with this name I went into a chat program called Virtual Places, within a few days I cam across a place called the Kingdom of Gwynedd. It had good people and they roleplayed a bit and it was sort of the thing I was into. So there I was. Now within a few days I had made a name for myself there and people smiled as I came in the room. So I began to have a place again. Now several things happened and Gwynedd fell to be reborn as Virtopia, and its King went from Uther to King Phoenix symbolizing this rebirth. ON this Rebirth I was Knighted and became the very first knight of the Kingdom and took the title of Captain, well after a time I became First Knight and things happened. Bad things mostly. Well as time went on I had to leave for a while and First Knight was taken over by another. When I came back the King Phoenix offered me to be his Hier and Prince to Virtopia as well as his Brother. So there I was Prince Darketernal.  <BR> Now as for Varden. I after a time became more at peace and that Darkness didn't seem so endless anymore. and in fact light showed in me. So I needed a name to reflect this. In the Silmarillion (Tolkien's work on the creation of middle earth and elves and men) there is described a female goddes type figure known as Varda. She was called the mother of the stars or something to that effect. And worshipped highly by the elves. So I thought perfect. I simply took the name and Masculinated it replacing a with the ending en. So there you have it.. Varden.  And that is my name to this day. <BR>  <BR> Prince Varden Darketernal of the Kingdom of Virtopia. Member of the Valor of Virtopia on the Povar server.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Sir Tolecnal duLac</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/4/00 4:48:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My Paladin's name - Tolecnal</span><hr size=1> One time playing AD&D our GM did a Arthurian legend adventure.  Not wanting us to figure out what type of adventure we were doing immediately, he spelled all the Arthurian legend NPC's names backwards.  As we discovered parallels to the real Arthurian legend, we finally figured out the names.  Boy I miss that GM, he was the best I've ever played with.  What an imagination and an ability to create word pictures to place you in the story... but I digress <BR>  <BR> Tolecnal = Lancelot <BR>  <BR> Humbly Sir Tolecnal du'Lac, a proud Paladin in real life also <BR>  <BR> In this world you are either good or evil, and the worst of these is neutral.  I trust good with my life and I distrust evil always, but neutral who was my friend has just killed me. <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uwildantor.showPublicProfile>Wildantor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/6/00 8:36:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did you get your Paladin name?</span><hr size=1> Neat thread Replay!  <BR>   <BR> Just stumbled across it.  :)  I usually only visit the other two boards.  :)  <BR>   <BR> And interesting where you got your name!  <BR>   <BR> For me:  <BR> ________  <BR>   <BR> I hit my Character Creation Screen...laid out all those little stats (sigh...if only I knew then what I do now.) and then came to the point where I had to name.  <BR>   <BR> And it sat there for a long time.  :)  <BR>   <BR> As I love GM'ing paper RPGs...I decided to come up with a back plot to help...  <BR>   <BR> I never have known my parents.  An orphan I am.  I was left on the steps of the temple of marr...raise up to be priest of Erollisi.  <BR>   <BR> After the great invasion of the undead areas of Faydwer...there were a lack of Paladins in the fine city of Freeport.  With Lucan running the rest of the town and forsaking his Paladin honor...the Temple was in some amount of danger.  <BR>   <BR> I changed my path from Priesthood to that of a Defender of the Temple.  A Knight of Truth.  <BR>   <BR> Now after all that...I still couldn't come up with a name.  :)  <BR>   <BR> So...After much banging my head against the wall.  I remembered from a Book I once read another estranged lad named &quot;Leldoran Wildantor&quot; (i'm not sure if I spelled his first name right...the last name might be off a little as well).  It was from a book by David Eddings...the kinda funny thing is...that gentleman was more of a ranger type.  <BR>   <BR> As I didn't want to pick a copy of his name.  I decided to go with his Last name as my First name.  <BR>   <BR> I've been very happy about it since.  People usually refer to me as Wild, or Wil now for short.  It has a nice feel to it...and fits the character quite well.  <BR>   <BR> As far as the last name.  <BR>   <BR> After some adventuring about it the world...Wildantor met up with a nice High Elf Wizard at the chessboard in BB.  Since then...they started just hanging around together alot.  <BR>   <BR> Eventually the got enganged.  And we decided to pick the last names together.  <BR>   <BR> I wanted 'Dal somewhere in the name...as 'Dal refers to Elf in Norath.  She came up with the Toran part...  <BR>   <BR> So...Toran'Dal it became.  Which is kinda neat I think...as it sounds like Tore-n...like its torn.  So I'm a Torn Elf...which being Half-Elf...is pretty neat!  And fitting my backstory as well.  <BR>   <BR> Perhaps someday I'll find my parents...maybe even a brother or two.  At this time...I choose not to seek them out.  <BR>   <BR> The Knights of Truth and those in the Temple of Marr are my brothers and sisters now.  I serve them to my best ability.  <BR>  <p>--<BR>Wildantor Toran'Dal<BR>Knight of Truth - Devoted Follower of Erollisi Marr<BR>GM of "Flame of Antiquity" Guild<BR>(Cazic-Thule)</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uwildantor.showPublicProfile>Wildantor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 1/6/00 1:28:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udador.showPublicProfile>Dador</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/6/00 9:42:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did you get your Paladin name?</span><hr size=1> My first name was not nearly so creative.  After a week of playing upon retail release, my first Paladin (Level 7) was lost down in the depths of Blackburrow, thanks to that stupid tree trap.  I decided to start over with a new character.  (Dador later fell down the darn pit in the middle, and rotted away as well.  That was back in the day when a level 10 was high for the game, and I didn't realize how easy it was to get him out of there.  I ended up fighting fire beetles bare-handed til I got enough money to buy a rusty sword.) <BR>  <BR> I made a new character.  When naming him, I simply used the name generator.  I kept clicking until I came up with something easy to spell and say.  At this point in my EQ gaming career, I had learned that although neat, names like Aaaklmincoih were difficult to type and a pain to remember easily.  I picked Rodcet Nife as my god, thinking that it might have some bearing on my character's ability to heal.   <BR>  <BR> My last name was much more creative.  My girlfriend was not really interested in EQ, but had asked me a few questions about my character to be polite.  At level 20, I told her he needed a last name.  I explained Paladins in general, and described their healing abilities.  She was once a nurse, and picked Caduceus.  She explained it was the symbol of the staff of healing (sort of).  It is usually seen in a doctor's office as the symbol with the 2 snakes.   <BR>  <BR> Plus, it went well with Dador.   <BR>  <BR> This was back in May or so.  Last month I came across the Cleric only mace called the Caduceus of Sacrament.  I emailed Verant asking about who designed, or thought of, this weapon and the story behind it.  After about a week I got back a personal (not cut and  paste) email saying no one knew who thought of this weapon or where the name came from.  Hmm, I still feel cheated. :) <BR>  <BR> Anyway, there's my story.   <BR>  <BR>  <BR>  <BR>  <p>Dador Caduceus<BR>Mithaniel Marr Server<BR>Realm of Valor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uoren.showPublicProfile>Oren</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/6/00 9:50:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did you get your Paladin name?</span><hr size=1> Heh, Oren is from a movie a saw while I was younger. The movie was called &quot;Flight of Dragons&quot; and Oren (Called Sir Orenevlsmive and Sir Oren) was a Knight that took down a Dragon by heaving his sword like a javalin into its belly. The sword took down the dragon becuase it was enveloped in the Dragon's own flame... <BR>  <BR> Anyway, My first game was Bards Tale...and I need a name for the Leader of the party. I used Oren. <BR>  <BR> Since then, (What 10 years ago? more?) I have used Oren...as a Knight / Paladin, in every character / party I have created. <BR>  <BR> From Bard's tale (I, II, III) Might N Magic, to Baldur's Gate and EQ, Oren has been a name that has stuck with me. <BR>  <BR> :) Nice Thread. Interesting reading others posts. <BR>  <BR> Sir Oren <BR> Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/unokomiskomali.showPublicProfile>Nokomis Komali</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/7/00 12:59:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did you get your Paladin name?</span><hr size=1> When my significant other & I first began seeing each other, within a day of our first kiss the night sky was blessed with the &quot;lovers moon&quot;.  It has been a running memory for us ever since... over 7 years now! <BR>  <BR> So - in finding a name for my EQ character (after realizing it was key for me to play in order to spend that time w/ my spouse) I spent a few hours searching 'baby name' sites looking for names that had a meaning I would enjoy carrying.  And, I happened upon Nokomis - Daughter of the moon.  This is of native american heritage, and I found out later that it is also the name of my mothers first baby doll, that she was given in Oklahoma.  (Not to mention there is also a perfume by the same name.)  It wasn't until I got setup in ICQ that I realized just how popular the name was. <BR>  <BR> As for the last name, I needed something to go with the first, and knowing that at 20 I'd get a last name, I picked it out before I ever created my char.  (without reading the rules on names etc..)  I chose Artemis, so that the full name in meaning would be Daughter of the moon goddess.  Pretty cool hu?  Welp, until you try to submit the surname... hehe <BR>  <BR> After months of playing & finally reaching 20 (and registering the full name on ezboard!) I found that Artemis was banished.  So... I revisited my search to those baby name sites... searching by meaning to find something cool.  I came up with a short list, narrowed it down to Kamali (spirit guide, protector) which matched closest to my reasons for picking Artemis.  Swap the first 'a' for an 'o', and it blends well with the first name. <BR>  <BR> There you have it...  <BR>  <BR> Noko *) <BR>  <BR> Guardians of K'Arnon <BR> Solusek Ro Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ugithnaurainaroquen.showPublicProfile>Githnaur Ainaroquen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/11/00 1:13:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did you get your Paladin name?</span><hr size=1> Many years ago, in the dusty days of 1200, 12/75, 2400 and heaven forbid, 9600 modems bbs' and suchlike I picked the alias Ghost, which I used for a few years, until the name became linked with some nefarious 'warez' cd's, and thought it wise to change the alias asap.  I used Etrigan for quite a while, the rhyming demon from the comic books - thankfully prior to the current crop of 'Demon' - the original 4 part series was superb (no i'm not a great comic fan, i just liked the original Demon, k :P). <BR>  <BR> I used this on most online systems as my alias, and various MUDs.  Until I came across EQ.  I found that someone had beaten me to it, and to be honest I am glad they did in many ways. <BR>  <BR> I fell back on the name I used in a long running tabletop RPG campaiugn I have been involved in, Githnaur.  A Paladin of Death, who trotted around slaying undead and suchlike.  The name itself came from scouring through a small tolkein dictionary, and lumping the words for 'gift' and 'death' together, and modifying it so it rolled off the tongue a little easier.  The general idea was supposed to be 'Gift of Death', laying tormented souls to rest etc. <BR>  <BR> On reaching 20th level I knew a surname was the order of the day, but not until 24th level did I finally choose one, when the 'love of Gith's life' got married to another and I no longer wished to leave the surname slot open (I can almost hear the violins now...hehe).   <BR>  <BR> I have heard many calling paladins 'tanks'..and in all honesty I didn't like the tag, correcting people whenever I was grouped that we were not tanks, but holy knights.  Ainaroquen is tolkein high-elven for holy knight.  I was told it was fitting, since I ragged on about it so much, and so it stuck. <BR>  <BR>  <p><img src="http://members.tripod.com/lostlegion/images/githsig.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usubatai.showPublicProfile>Subatai</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/18/00 10:05:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladin